The third ReplanEU seminar within the cycle of seminars "Caffé Europa" entitled "L'Europa e il rapporto tra l'uomo e l'ambiente" took place on Thursday 17 November 17:30 at the Campus bookshop. I talked about how energy communities can help to tackle climate change and the impact of NextGenerationEU to foster their implementation with Francesco Grasso (docente Università degli Studi di Firenze), Simone Tartaro (Coordinatore Regionale Energia presso ARRR - Agenzia Regionale Recupero Risorse) e Irene Fattacciu (ricercatrice del centro di ricerca ARCO). The event was organised in collaboration with Europedirect Firenze, Ponte Europa, EUI and Unifi CDE.

